Cell.Data: Record of medication being taken by a patient
NB does not currently support applicable CeRX Message Type(s)

CeRX supports two specializations of MedicationRecord, each varies in supported data. Both mappings provided below: PORX_IN060400CA/PORX_MT060190CA/medicationRecord/combinedMedicationRequest OR PORX_IN060400CA/PORX_MT060190CA/medicationRecord/OtherMedication

CeRX supports two specializations of MedicationRecord, each varies in supported data. Both mappings provided below: PORX_IN060400CA/PORX_MT060190CA/medicationRecord/combinedMedicationRequest OR PORX_IN060400CA/PORX_MT060190CA/medicationRecord/OtherMedication

CeRX supports two specializations of MedicationRecord, each varies in supported data. Both mappings provided below: PORX_IN060400CA/PORX_MT060190CA/medicationRecord/combinedMedicationRequest OR PORX_IN060400CA/PORX_MT060190CA/medicationRecord/OtherMedication
active | completed | entered-in-error | intended | stopped | on-hold | unknown | not-taken | normal | aborted | cancelled | held | new | suspended | nullified | obsolete

This element is labeled as a modifier because the status contains codes that mark the resource as not currently valid. Atlantic Implementors need to be aware that the Act Status Codes recommended by CeRX only partially match the codes to the MedicationRequest status (required) value set

If only a code is specified, then it needs to be a code for a specific product. If more information is required, then the use of the Medication resource is recommended. For example, if you require form or lot number or if the medication is compounded or extemporaneously prepared, then you must reference the Medication resource.
Implementors need to be aware that the medication codes utilized by the source DIS will likely come from the Clinical Drug CeRX value set (https://infocentral.infoway-inforoute.ca/extra/ns/cerx43-html/html/vocabulary.html?type=vs&id=ClinicalDrug) which draws in codes from various other code systems (HC-DIN, HC-NPN, HC-AIGC, etc.). There is currently no equivilant FHIR value set that supports this superset to recommend when binding.

Cell.Data: A coded value denoting drug identification at various levels of abstraction. Examples include identification system for manufactured drug product, generic formulation, generic, and therapeutic class.
This value set includes some taken and not taken reason codes from SNOMED CT - provided as an exemplar

This value set includes content from SNOMED CT, which is copyright © 2002+ International Health Terminology Standards Development Organisation (IHTSDO), and distributed by agreement between IHTSDO and HL7. Implementer use of SNOMED CT is not covered by this agreement
Example value set for Condition/Problem/Diagnosis codes.
Codes used to identify different types of 'duration-based' working lists. Examples include "Continuous/Chronic", "Short-Term" and "As-Needed".
The set of body locations to or through which a drug product may be administered.
This is the means by which a substance is to be admiinistered to the patient.
Identifies the types of substitution that may be permitted when ordering a medication, as well as those which have actually occurred during the act of dispensing.
Indicates the reason for substitution when substitution is not expected, or reason for non-substitution when substitution is expected.
Contains a set of coordinated information related to a diagnosis or health condition.
This value set includes all drug or medicament substance codes and all pharmaceutical/biologic products from SNOMED CT - provided as an exemplar value set.
